Cumberland County conducts Naturalization Court once a year in the Ceremonial Courtroom on the second floor of the Old Courthouse.
Delaware County Judges have the honor of formally greeting America's newest citizens and administering their oaths of Naturalization during four programs held at the Courthouse each year.
For information about scheduling or rescheduling a naturalization ceremony, contact the U.S. Citizenship and Immigration Services at (800) 375-5283.
